==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Birmingham]], [[England]] where cheap manufactured goods used to be produced.
===Adjective===
'''brummagem'''
#[[Cheap]] and [[showy]], or [[meretricious]].
#*'''1999''': "My, my, my, my, my," said a voice from behind them, and the Baudelaire orphans turned to find Stephano standing there,...a look of '''brummagem''' surprise on his face. "Brummagem" is such a rare word for "fake" that even Klaus didn't know what it meant, but the children did not have to be told that Stephano was pretending to be surprised.  -- '''The Reptile Room''', Lemony Snicket.
#*'''1999''':  He stomped over to where Mr. Poe was standing, but halfway there the children saw his face change from one of pure rage to one of '''brummagem''' confusion and sadness. -- ''ibid''.

